'''''Tyalië Tyelelliéva''''' is a journal on Tolkienian linguistics edited by [[Lisa Star]] since [[1994]]. It publishes poems and other texts in the Elvish languages as well as articles about the languages and alphabets of [[Middle-earth]].  

It appeared three to four times per year at first, but after November [[1995]], issues appeared more irregularly, roughly twice per year, before the current hiatus in publication began in December [[2001]]. How long this hiatus will last is unknown - no-one seems to be able to contact her<ref>Matthew "Tyrhael" Dinse, [http://groups.yahoo.com/group/elfling/message/34824 Message 34824], ''[[Elfling]]''</ref> - but the official website received an update in March [[2009]].
